docs.abstract: Despite voicing deference to the speaker, a growing number of Senate Democrats said that they were losing patience with the delay and wanted the trial to begin.
docs.snippet: Despite voicing deference to the speaker, a growing number of Senate Democrats said that they were losing patience with the delay and wanted the trial to begin.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Mitch McConnell, the majority leader, insisted on Wednesday that Speaker Nancy Pelosi accept his terms for President Trump’s impeachment trial and promptly deliver the charges from the House, as a growing number of Senate Democrats signaled that they, too, were eager to begin the proceeding.

headline.main: McConnell, Rebuffing Pelosi, Declines to Budge on Impeachment Trial Terms
headline.print_headline: ‘No Haggling’ on Terms Of Impeachment Trial, McConnell Tells Pelosi

docs.abstract: The Agriculture Department proposed a rule that would further unravel nutrition standards set by Mrs. Obama when she was first lady.
docs.snippet: The Agriculture Department proposed a rule that would further unravel nutrition standards set by Mrs. Obama when she was first lady.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration moved on Friday to roll back school nutrition standards championed by Michelle Obama, an effort long sought by food manufacturers and some school districts that have chafed at the cost of Mrs. Obama’s prescriptions for fresh fruit and vegetables.

headline.main: Trump Targets Michelle Obama’s School Nutrition Guidelines on Her Birthday
headline.print_headline: U.S.D.A. Tries To Relax Rules On School Food

docs.abstract: Texts raised more questions about information suggesting that the United States ambassador to Ukraine was under surveillance.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats released another round of information on Friday that raised questions about elements of the impeachment inquiry, including allegations about the surveillance of the United States ambassador in Ukraine and efforts by an aide to a top congressional Republican to pursue investigations sought by President Trump.

headline.main: Democrats Release More Material From Lev Parnas on Ukraine Campaign
headline.print_headline: Parnas’s Texts Tie Nunes’s Aide to Ukraine Efforts

docs.abstract: Lawmakers challenged President Trump’s reluctance to send more aid to Puerto Rico, unveiling $3.35 billion in funding.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House lawmakers introduced an emergency aid package on Thursday to help Puerto Rico rebuild after earthquakes devastated the already storm-battered island, challenging President Trump, who has resisted further assistance for the commonwealth.

docs.abstract: A call for civility by Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. underscores the delicate balance he is trying to maintain.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It was early Wednesday morning, and Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. had had enough. He had been listening to increasingly acid exchanges at the impeachment trial of President Trump, and he was ready to chastise the House managers and the president’s lawyers.

headline.main: Rebuke From Roberts Signals His Limited Role in Trump’s Senate Trial
